blockrun-cli — harness fixes + delta RED coverage (post-Green escalation)
==========================================================================

Context: impl-builder's Green phase landed 363/367 passing and escalated 4 failures as
TEST-FILE defects (not implementation bugs), per .vcsdd/features/blockrun-cli/evidence/
sprint-1-green-phase.log and req-135a-manual-verification.log. Fixed both below, then
added the requested delta RED coverage for three implemented-but-previously-untested
areas (Solana image, chat native anthropic, chat routing:smart).

1) HARNESS FIXES (assertions unchanged, only the test mechanics were broken):

   a. test/cli/video-max-quote-usd.test.ts — switched spawnSync -> async spawn + await.
      spawnSync blocks the parent process's event loop synchronously until the child
      exits; since the stub node:http server runs IN-PROCESS (same event loop), the
      server's request handler could never fire while spawnSync was blocking — the
      child's own fetch timed out waiting for a response that would never come. Also
      fixed the stub's fixture payTo address, which was 38 hex chars (one byte short of
      a valid 20-byte address) -> corrected to the real 40-hex-char "dead address"
      (0x000000000000000000000000000000000000dEaD) so viem's getAddress() (used inside
      the SDK's real createPaymentPayload, REQ-221/222) accepts it.
      Result: all 3 sub-tests now pass (previously deadlocked -> 15s timeout failures).

   b. test/integration/video.test.ts "REQ-133" — `(chainModule as any).getChain = ...`
      illegally reassigned a property on a non-writable ES module namespace object.
      Replaced with the file's own established pattern: a mutable `activeChain`
      variable read by the mock.module()'d getChain(), flipped per-test instead of
      mutating the imported namespace after the fact.
      Result: passes (previously threw TypeError: Cannot assign to read only property).

2) NEW RED/GREEN coverage for three previously-untested areas:

   a. Solana image payment (REQ-220) — test/integration/image.test.ts, 2 new tests.
      The impl for this landed on the shared working tree WHILE this fix round was in
      progress (src/commands/image.ts + src/shell/solana-x402.ts, mirroring
      blockrun-mcp's solana-402.ts and using the SDK's real createSolanaPaymentPayload).
      Both new tests PASS against the real implementation:
        - a quote within the budget cap signs and reports the REAL 402-quoted cost
          (not the Base catalog estimate).
        - a quote that exceeds the cap ($15 real quote vs a $0.02 cap) aborts BEFORE
          any charge is recorded, proving the onQuote/reverify gate fires before
          createSolanaPaymentPayload is ever reached (REQ-220's core requirement).

   b. chat routing:"smart" (REQ-111/112/118) — test/integration/chat.test.ts, 3 new
      tests. All PASS: smartChat(message, options) dispatch with routing_profile
      threaded through; routing_profile:"free" maps to undefined (SDK dropped the free
      profile) rather than a literal string; Solana is rejected before any network call.

   c. chat native anthropic/claude-* passthrough (REQ-117, REQ-114/114a) —
      test/integration/chat.test.ts, 4 new tests. 3 PASS: native routing to
      messages.create (not llm.chat) on an anthropic/claude-* model; Base-only guard
      (Solana rejected, messages.create never called); --thinking-budget-tokens compiles
      into the native thinking object correctly.

      1 FAILS — a REAL implementation gap, not a test-authoring bug: "the native
      response's thinking block AND its signature are preserved verbatim in the CLI's
      output". src/commands/chat.ts's native-anthropic branch does
      `content?.find(b => b.type === "text")?.text` and returns ONLY that extracted
      text as `{model_used, response}` — it silently discards any `type:"thinking"`
      content block (and its `signature` field) from the response entirely. REQ-117
      requires "route natively (verbatim thinking blocks/signatures)" — the routing
      IS native and correct, but the response is not verbatim; the thinking block is
      dropped, not passed through. Reported to team-lead as a genuine Green-phase gap,
      not weakened/skipped per the project's testing rule.

Full suite: `npm test` -> 375 pass / 1 fail (up from 363/367 pre-fix; the 4 escalated
failures are now 0, plus 9 new passing tests and 1 new legitimately-failing test for the
REQ-117 gap above).
